<p class="lead">How to preserve the file last modification date?</p>
<p>
Unfortunately, web browsers ignore the last modification date metadata when it is attached to a file download.
However, you can use other tools such as wget or curl for downloading to preserve the date.
</p>
<p>
For example, the artifact "<a href="/f/b32455c">SYMCOLOR.COR</a>" was last modified in November 1985, to download and preserve it on your system,
</p>
wget <code>--content-disposition https://defacto2.net/d/b32455c</code><br> 
curl <code>-LOJR https://defacto2.net/d/b32455c</code>
</p>
<pre>
  Saving 'SYMCOLOR.COR'
  HTTP response 200 OK [https://defacto2.net/d/b32455c]
  SYMCOLOR.COR         100%

$ ls -l SYMCOLOR.COR
  2560 Nov 28  1985  SYMCOLOR.COR
</pre>
