<p class="lead">Shrinker.err Dispatcher initialization errors</p>
<p>
An ancient Windows program crashes with the cryptic error message.
</p>
<p>
This is a common error that occurs with Windows 9x applications that are compressed with earlier versions of the Shrinker compression library. 
Fortunately, there is an easy solution with decompressing the application using either DeShrink 1.6 or UnShrinker. 
DeShrink is a standard Windows application, while UnShrinker uses the command prompt.
</p>
<p>
There will be occasions where these solutions cannot decrypt or fix the affected programs. 
In these circumstances, you will not be able to solve this issue other than to run the applications generating the Dispatcher error on a Windows 95, 98, or ME system.
</p>
